Job Responsibilities:

Assist in Procurement operational functions such as product sourcing and vendor selection of food & non-food items;
Provide administrative & clerical support to procurement team;
Prepare documentation of relevant purchasing activities including price comparisons, purchasing order, and market price surveys;
Assist in the coordination of all product and purchase specifications from business units;
Conduct interviews as required by Procurement Manager with suppliers’ representatives to obtain information, specifications, and quotations and to negotiate to the best advantage of the Group;
Assist in ad hoc projects as assigned.

Job Requirements:

Diploma or above in Purchase and Supply Chain Management or related discipline;
Min. 1 year relevant experience in F&B industry;
Proficiency in computer skills;
Self-motivated, ability to work under pressure, good team player, good communications skills in Chinese & English.

Much more experienced candidate will be considered for the post of Procurement Officer.

Interested parties please apply with full resume with date of availability and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now"

(Personal data collected will be kept strictly confidential and to be used for recruitment purposes only.)

Reporting to the Head, Museum Retail and Commerce, the role of Senior Manager, Museum Retail Merchandising is key to ensuring the delivery of a truly unique M+ cultural retail experience.  Through the creation, purchase and visual merchandising of extraordinary product offerings, the incumbent will deliver an on-brand message to all visitor type to ensure revenue maximization.

You will be responsible for :

working closely with the Head, Museum Retail & Commerce, develop and implement the museum’s product development, procurement and retail sales strategy for all retail outlets including online platforms;
representing the retail merchandising function across the museum, understanding museum programmes and activities and identifying retail sales opportunities; 
managing overall retail budget, ensuring the allocation, spending and income are within the approved scope and for the best interest of M+;
developing and maintaining the requisite structures, systems and procedures in order to facilitate the implementation of the agreed strategies;
leading the team to manage the retail and buying activities, product development, supply chain, ecommerce and business development for the museum, aiming to drive the profitability through agreed strategies;
driving the product development process, efficiently procuring and launching new products to align with the collections and activities of the museum;
ensuring that core ranges of merchandise are procured efficiently, maximising sale and profitability and ensuring that they are aligned with the collections and activities of the museum;
working with the retail sales manager to ensure the highest level of visual merchandising and window displays are achieved;
developing sales and promotional programmes that maximizes sales opportunities with exhibitions, museum activities and customer seasonality while maximizing margins and minimizing mark downs to ensure inventory levels are always kept at acceptable levels;
developing workshop, product launches and other community engagement opportunities as they arise with merchandising strategy;
managing supplier relationships to ensure high service levels and optimum terms and conditions; and
working closely with other departments to ensure smooth operations of the team.
You should :
possess a recognised university degree in any disciplines;
have at least 10 years of experience with multi-national lifestyle retailers which 5 years at managerial position;
demonstrate strong project management skill, business acumen and numerical sense to drive large volume of retail and merchandising function;
possess strong leadership capability and attributes which aim to deliver the best business result and team management;
possess strong negotiation, influencing and collaboration skills, able to work with a number of stakeholders to drive result and achieve the targets; and
have good communication skills, be proficient in both written and oral English and Chinese.
For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed CV on or before 12 January 2022. Applicants are encouraged to submit their applications as soon as possible. The review of applications will continue until post is filled.

Data collected will only be used for job application processing. Your data may be accessed by our appointed recruitment consultants who have agreed to keep confidence of all personal data in not less than the standards applicable to us.

Applicants not being invited for interview within 4 weeks from the submission date may assume their applications unsuccessful.

All related information will be kept up to 24 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.

